ges (Harris, Enever, Carmel). The book is a must have for teacher educators of pre- and in-service teachers of modern languages to young learners, MA and PhD students in TEFL/TESOL and other languages, researchers and policy makers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aBilingualism in children. 0aLanguage acquisitionxAge factors. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching. 0aSecond language acquisition. 4aAngewandte Linguisitk. 4aSprachdidaktik. 4aSpracherwerb. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aApplied Linguistics.  aLanguage Teaching.  aSecond Language Acquisition.1 aAlexiou, Thomaï, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarmel, Rivi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCurtain, Helena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdelenbos, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEnever, Janet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarris, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeinzmann, Sybille, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoti, Andrea Haenni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInbar-Lourie, Ofra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJalkanen, Joanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKasai, Chise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKiss, Csilla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKubanek, Angelika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMattheoudakis, Marina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMihaljević Djigunović, Jelen